Thailand Stocks: MFC Asset, Sri Trang Agro, Thai Rubber Latex

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-03-22T05:58:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/thailand-stocks-mfc-asset-management-sri-trang-agro-industry.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 2.05, or 0.2 percent, to 1,021.98.  Rubber producers:  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  ,
Thailand’s biggest publicly traded rubber producer, gained 3.7
percent to 28 baht, poised for the highest level since March 10.
Thai Rubber Latex Corp. (Thailand) Pcl (TRUBB TB) climbed 1.7
percent to 6.10 baht.  Rubber futures in  Tokyo  jumped for a fourth day on
expectation demand will exceed declining supplies during the
low-production period, and as a producer group moved to boost
prices. Rubber futures in Tokyo jumped as much as 5.1 percent to
429.6 yen a kilogram today.  MFC Asset Management Pcl (MFC)   surged 19 percent to 17.8
baht, set for the highest close since May 9, 2007. The company
said it plans to pay a cash dividend of 2.9 baht per share.    Siam Industrial Credit Pcl (SICCO)  , a financial
company, climbed 2.7 percent to 4.58 baht, bound for the highest
close since Aug. 31. The shares rose 6.2 percent yesterday.  Siam
Commercial Bank Pcl (SCB)  , Siam Industrial’s biggest
shareholder, plans to hold a public auction for its stake in the
financial company, it said in a regulatory filing yesterday.
Siam Commercial, Thailand’s fourth-biggest lender by assets,
fell 1 percent to 103 baht.  -- Editor: Shiyin Chen  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
